-- Jefferies reports loss, seeks options for brokerage unit
-- By Amrutha Gayathri in Bengaluru
-- Tue Dec 16, 2014 08:14AM EST
-- None



Dec 16 (Reuters) - Investment bank Jefferies Group LLC, owned by Leucadia National Corp <LUK.N>, reported a quarterly loss and said it was exploring strategic alternatives for its futures-brokerage unit.

Net loss attributable to the company was $92.4 million for the fourth quarter ended Nov. 30, compared with a profit of $109.9 million a year earlier, the company said on Tuesday. [ID:nBw7wsN1ha] Net revenue fell about 43 percent to $537.6 million.